cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.PL

This paper discusses the usability of security APIs, specifically the SCrypt password hashing functionality of Bouncycastle API. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves a study with programmers, which suggests a possible fit with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and development of security/cryptographic APIs, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of password storage, which could relate to cs.CY (Cybersecurity).
